CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1955, pg. 19 reads: "Custom Built Home - This attractive dwelling was built on Ewart Drive by Bevefly [sic] Hunt for Mr. and Mrs. Jody Harris. This home reflects kind of custom building in which Mr. Hunt has won himself a reputation fro sound construction to meet the demands of prospective home owners who want a house erected to their own specifications, rather than to adapt their family to a home designed simply to please most people."
TitMainTitle: Two story half brick home of the Jody Harris' with single attached garage with maple leaf decoration, door with small square window, and picture window, 3161 Ewart Drive
